The second season of Hataraku Maou-sama! MgRonald’s best demon lord worker is back, climbing the corporate ladder to become ruler of Earth. But Maou’s plans of domination might need to be put on hold when a small girl claims to be his and Emi’s child! (Source: Crunchyroll)
Keikenzumi na Kimi to, Keiken Zero na Ore ga, Otsukiai suru Hanashi.

Ryuuto Kashima is the school’s gloomy introvert, and he’s got a crush on Runa Shirakawa, the popular girl. After losing a bet to classmates, he confesses his feelings to Runa one day. Shocked and secretly just as inexperienced as Ryuuto, Runa agrees to date him. The relationship grows between two people who are as similar as they are different. Will their young love blossom? Time will tell!
(Source: Crunchyroll)

Nega Shouya and Hoshi Sayaka are high school classmates. Nega is tremendously pessimistic, while Hoshi is optimistic, both to a fault. They also happen to be deeply in love with each other, but they completely misread each other's cues, him erring by defect, and her erring by excess. The fundamental law of magnetism states that opposites attract, and these two starkly different young lovers are not the exception! (Source: Kadokawa, translated) Note: Includes 5 extra chapters.

Shizuku Hayama is the personal bodyguard for Ichika Kiryuin, the only daughter of a major industrialist. But Ichika is no shrinking violet, and she's perfectly able to handle any dangerous situation or challenge by herself. If Ichika doesn't need anyone protect her body, maybe Shizuku can help to protect her heart?
